	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How comes so many NES games were ported to MSX ?</div><br />I guess games were ported to C64, MSX, etc. because even ColecoVision/SG-1000 style 1bpp sprites were better sprites than other home computers available in Japan and other MSX markets had at the time. Not everybody who could afford an 8-bit home computer could also afford a separate game console, and some MSX markets had much higher import duties for dedicated game consoles than for home computers.

		

